# Study Abroad Platform — Frontend API Reference

This document lists all backend API endpoints, their expected inputs, and their response formats. It is intended for frontend developers integrating with the Study Abroad backend.

---

## General Notes

- **Base URL:** `https://your-backend-domain.com` (replace with actual deployment URL)
- **Auth:** All endpoints except `/auth/signup` and `/auth/login` require an `Authorization` header:
  ```
  Authorization: Bearer <access_token>
  ```
- **Content Type:** All REST requests use `Content-Type: application/json` unless marked as `multipart/form-data`.
- **WebSocket Auth:** Pass the JWT as a query parameter since browser WebSockets do not support custom headers:
  ```
  ws://your-backend-domain.com/session/{session_id}/stream?token=<access_token>
  ```
- **Roles:** Some endpoints are restricted to `admin` role only. These are marked with 🔒 Admin Only.

