## 1. Auth

### `POST /auth/signup`
Register a new student account.

**Request:**
```json
{
  "email": "riya@example.com",
  "password": "SecurePass123!",
  "full_name": "Riya Sharma",
  "role": "student"
}
```

**Response `200`:**
```json
{
  "user_id": "uuid",
  "email": "riya@example.com",
  "role": "student",
  "access_token": "eyJ...",
  "token_type": "bearer"
}
```

---

### `POST /auth/login`
Log in and receive tokens.

**Request:**
```json
{
  "email": "riya@example.com",
  "password": "SecurePass123!"
}
```

**Response `200`:**
```json
{
  "access_token": "eyJ...",
  "refresh_token": "eyJ...",
  "token_type": "bearer",
  "user_id": "uuid",
  "role": "student"
}
```

> Store both tokens. Use `access_token` for all API calls. Use `refresh_token` to get a new access token when it expires.

---

### `POST /auth/logout`
Invalidate the current session.

**Request:** No body required. Just send the `Authorization` header.

**Response `200`:**
```json
{
  "message": "Logged out successfully"
}
```

---

### `POST /auth/refresh`
Get a new access token using the refresh token.

**Request:**
```json
{
  "refresh_token": "eyJ..."
}
```

**Response `200`:**
```json
{
  "access_token": "eyJ...",
  "token_type": "bearer"
}
```

---

### `GET /auth/me`
Get the currently logged-in user's basic info and role.

**Request:** No body. Send `Authorization` header.

**Response `200`:**
```json
{
  "user_id": "uuid",
  "email": "riya@example.com",
  "full_name": "Riya Sharma",
  "role": "student"
}
```

