## 3. Session — REST

### `POST /session/create`
Create a new counselling session. Returns the session ID and WebRTC ICE server config needed to start the call.

**Request:**
```json
{
  "user_id": "uuid",
  "preferred_language": "auto"
}
```

**Response `200`:**
```json
{
  "session_id": "uuid",
  "user_id": "uuid",
  "status": "created",
  "webrtc_config": {
    "ice_servers": [
      { "urls": "stun:stun.l.google.com:19302" },
      { "urls": "stun:stun1.l.google.com:19302" }
    ]
  },
  "created_at": "2025-04-04T10:05:00Z"
}
```

> Use `webrtc_config.ice_servers` directly when initialising `RTCPeerConnection` on the frontend.

---

### `GET /session/{session_id}`
Get metadata and current status of a session.

**Request:** No body.

**Response `200`:**
```json
{
  "session_id": "uuid",
  "user_id": "uuid",
  "status": "active",
  "language_detected": "hi",
  "started_at": "2025-04-04T10:06:00Z",
  "duration_seconds": null
}
```

> `duration_seconds` is `null` while the session is active. It is populated after the session ends.

---

### `GET /session/{session_id}/status`
Lightweight status check. Use this to poll whether the session has ended or a report is ready.

**Request:** No body.

**Response `200`:**
```json
{
  "status": "created"
}
```

> Possible values: `"created"` `"active"` `"ended"` `"failed"`

---

### `POST /session/{session_id}/end`
Signal that the session has ended. Call this when the user clicks "End Call" or when the WebSocket closes. Triggers background report generation.

**Request:** No body.

**Response `200`:**
```json
{
  "message": "Session ended. Report generation in progress.",
  "session_id": "uuid",
  "status": "ended"
}
```

