## 4. Session — WebSocket

### `WS /session/{session_id}/signal`
WebRTC signaling channel. Used to exchange SDP offer/answer and ICE candidates. Opens, completes the handshake, then closes automatically.

**Connection URL:**
```
ws://your-backend-domain.com/session/{session_id}/signal?token=<access_token>
```

---

**Messages you SEND (Frontend → Backend):**

SDP Offer:
```json
{
  "type": "offer",
  "sdp": "v=0\r\no=- ..."
}
```

ICE Candidate:
```json
{
  "type": "ice_candidate",
  "candidate": "candidate:842163049 1 udp ...",
  "sdpMid": "0",
  "sdpMLineIndex": 0
}
```

---

**Messages you RECEIVE (Backend → Frontend):**

SDP Answer:
```json
{
  "type": "answer",
  "sdp": "v=0\r\no=- ..."
}
```

ICE Candidate from server:
```json
{
  "type": "ice_candidate",
  "candidate": "candidate:842163049 1 udp ...",
  "sdpMid": "0",
  "sdpMLineIndex": 0
}
```

Ready signal (signaling complete, session is now active):
```json
{
  "type": "ready"
}
```

Error:
```json
{
  "type": "error",
  "message": "Signaling failed"
}
```

---

### `WS /session/{session_id}/stream`
The main real-time bidirectional channel. Stays open for the entire call. Send audio and video chunks here. Receive AI audio responses and live transcript text here.

**Connection URL:**
```
ws://your-backend-domain.com/session/{session_id}/stream?token=<access_token>
```

---

**Messages you SEND (Frontend → Backend):**

Audio chunk (raw PCM, 16kHz mono, encoded as base64):
```json
{
  "type": "audio_chunk",
  "data": "<base64-encoded-pcm>",
  "timestamp_ms": 1234
}
```

Video frame (JPEG snapshot from webcam, encoded as base64):
```json
{
  "type": "video_frame",
  "data": "<base64-jpeg>",
  "timestamp_ms": 1234
}
```

End session signal (send when the user clicks End Call):
```json
{
  "type": "session_end_signal"
}
```

---

**Messages you RECEIVE (Backend → Frontend):**

AI audio response (play this through the speaker):
```json
{
  "type": "audio_response",
  "data": "<base64-pcm>",
  "timestamp_ms": 1234
}
```

Transcript chunk — AI speaking (display in chat/subtitle UI):
```json
{
  "type": "transcript_chunk",
  "speaker": "ai",
  "text": "नमस्ते! आप किस देश में पढ़ना चाहते हैं?",
  "language": "hi",
  "timestamp_ms": 0
}
```

Transcript chunk — User speaking (display in chat/subtitle UI):
```json
{
  "type": "transcript_chunk",
  "speaker": "user",
  "text": "मैं Germany सोच रहा हूँ।",
  "language": "hi",
  "timestamp_ms": 4500
}
```

Language detected (update UI language indicator):
```json
{
  "type": "language_detected",
  "language": "hi"
}
```

> Possible `language` values: `"en"` `"hi"` `"mr"`

Session status update:
```json
{
  "type": "session_status",
  "status": "active"
}
```

```json
{
  "type": "session_status",
  "status": "ended"
}
```

Error:
```json
{
  "type": "error",
  "code": "GEMINI_STREAM_FAIL",
  "message": "Gemini relay encountered an error"
}
```

> **Note:** Transcript chunks are for display only. The backend does not store them. If the user closes the tab, the transcript is gone.

